29/04/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- UN envoy Matthew Nimetz summoned Greek and Macedonian representatives to separate consultations in New York aimed at resolving the name dispute between the two countries, Greek and Macedonian media reported on Monday (April 28th). 
Sources say Macedonian envoy Nikola Dimitrov meets with Nimetz on Tuesday and Wednesday, while consultations with Greek representative Adamantios Vassilakis will occur Wednesday and Thursday. 
No joint meetings between Dimitrov and Vassilakis are on the agenda. 
(Dnevnik, Sky - 29/04/08; Makfax, Kanal 5, A1 - 28/04/08)
